theorem Topology.dense_iff_interior_complement_eq_empty {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X]
    {A : Set X} :
    Dense (A : Set X) ↔ interior ((A : Set X)ᶜ) = (∅ : Set X) := by
  constructor
  · intro hDense
    -- `closure A = univ`, hence its complement is empty.
    have h_cl : closure (A : Set X) = (Set.univ : Set X) := hDense.closure_eq
    -- `interior (Aᶜ) = (closure A)ᶜ`.
    have h_eq : interior ((A : Set X)ᶜ) = (closure (A : Set X))ᶜ := by
      simpa using interior_compl
    -- Rewrite using `h_cl`.
    simpa [h_cl] using h_eq
  · intro hIntEmpty
    -- Show every point belongs to `closure A`.
    dsimp [Dense]
    intro x
    by_contra hx
    -- `x` lies in the open set `(closure A)ᶜ`, which is contained in `Aᶜ`.
    have hx_compl : (x : X) ∈ ((closure (A : Set X))ᶜ : Set X) := hx
    have h_open : IsOpen ((closure (A : Set X))ᶜ : Set X) :=
      (isClosed_closure : IsClosed (closure (A : Set X))).isOpen_compl
    have h_subset :
        ((closure (A : Set X))ᶜ : Set X) ⊆ (A : Set X)ᶜ := by
      intro y hy; exact hy
    -- Hence `x ∈ interior (Aᶜ)`, contradicting `hIntEmpty`.
    have hx_int : (x : X) ∈ interior ((A : Set X)ᶜ) :=
      (interior_maximal h_subset h_open) hx_compl
    simpa [hIntEmpty] using hx_int

theorem Topology.interior_inter_open {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A B : Set X}
    (hA : IsOpen (A : Set X)) (hB : IsOpen (B : Set X)) :
    interior ((A ∩ B) : Set X) = A ∩ B := by
  have h_open : IsOpen ((A ∩ B) : Set X) := hA.inter hB
  simpa using h_open.interior_eq
